Ah, %PLAYERNAME%—I’ve got news. The leaders of Team GO Rocket—Arlo, Cliff, and Sierra—have been spotted in the area.
We still don’t know what their plans are for the Dynamax phenomenon, but whatever they are, those three will be carrying them out!
Follow the leaders and find out what they’re up to—and stop them, if necessary!
I’ll be mapping out our next move—I think I’ll have something by the time you’ve dealt with the leaders. Good luck!
It looks like my suspicions were correct—this goes all the way to the top: Giovanni.
We’ve got to put a stop to his schemes, and I know you’re the perfect Trainer to do just that.
Go and show him what you’re made of!
Excellent work! Couldn’t have done better myself!
I’m too familiar with Team GO Rocket to believe we’ve heard the last of Giovanni, but you’ve definitely thrown a wrench into their plans.
I want to check in on nearby Dynamax Pokémon, so please take care of any Team GO Rocket Grunts still hanging around.
Great job, %PLAYERNAME%! The Dynamax Pokémon are safe now, thanks to your courage and skill.
We’ll need to keep a close eye on Team GO Rocket as we keep up our research on the Dynamax phenomenon, though.
Call it a professor’s intuition, but I’ve got a feeling a gigantic discovery is just around the corner.
%PLAYERNAME%, I’m glad you’re here. I’ve been bombarded with reports of Team GO Rocket sightings!
Those troublemakers are up to something. I’m sure of it.
Let me know what you find out, and I’ll keep you updated on my end. And stay safe out there!
Glad you’re back. I’ve been reviewing these Team GO Rocket reports, and I think I’ve pieced together something troubling.
The evidence suggests that they’re trying to take advantage of the Dynamax phenomenon.
Can you imagine the chaos if they could harness that kind of power? We can’t let that happen!
Please stop Team GO Rocket from getting anywhere near any Dynamax Pokémon!

You can find some by spinning Photo Discs at PokéStops and Gyms.

Also, Pokémon GO Wild Area ticket holders receive premium Timed Research that awards GO Safari Balls each hour.
GO Safari Balls are great for catching mighty Pokémon!

Includes: • An encounter with Toxtricity, the Punk Pokémon • Up to 5 free Raid Passes each day from spinning Gym Photo Discs • Increased chance of Toxel hatching from 10 km Eggs • Up to 6 Special Trades per day and reduced Stardust cost for trades • 1/2 Egg Hatch Distance • 2× Candy for catching Pokémon • A higher chance to encounter Shiny Pokémon during the event • Purchase by October 22 and play between October 15 and October 22 for Timed Research that awards the Toxel Mask avatar item! Learn more about the ticket bonuses here.

A ticket to Pokémon GO Wild Area: Global, which has been provided to you early and at no cost. Includes: • An encounter with Toxtricity, the Punk Pokémon • Up to 5 free Raid Passes each day from spinning Gym Photo Discs • Increased chance of Toxel hatching from 10 km Eggs • Up to 6 Special Trades per day and reduced Stardust cost for trades • 1/2 Egg Hatch Distance • 2× Candy for catching Pokémon • A higher chance to encounter Shiny Pokémon during the event • Purchase by October 22 and play between October 15 and October 22 for Timed Research that awards the Toxel Mask avatar item! Learn more about the ticket bonuses here.

Included rewards: • One Master Ball—a Poké Ball that can catch any wild Pokémon without fail • Encounters with Galarian Weezing, Galarian Farfetch’d, Galarian Mr. Mime, and Galarian Stunfisk • 18,000 XP and 10,000 Stardust • Premium in-game items such as Ultra Balls, Silver Pinap Berries, and Charged TMs

Included bonuses: • Eight additional Raid Passes from spinning Photo Discs at Gyms • Increased chance to receive Rare Candy XL from raids • 50% more XP and 2× Stardust for successfully completing raids

This ticket grants bonuses, Timed Research awarding 200 bonus PokéCoins, and daily bonus Field Research tasks that award bonus PokéCoins from November 3 to December 2, 2024. Included bonuses: • One Field Research task the first time you log on each day that awards 20 bonus PokéCoins • 3× XP for your first catch of the day and your first spin of the day • Open up to 50 Gifts a day • Collect up to 150 Gifts a day from PokéStops and Gyms • Hold up to 40 Gifts in your Item Bag at once Please note: You must have three or fewer Field Research tasks active to receive this bonus Field Research task the first time you log on each day. You must claim the 20 bonus PokéCoin reward after completing the task to receive it. You can learn more about bonus Field Research tasks here.
Included rewards: • Encounters with Morelull and Hatenna • 15,000 XP • 1 Incubator, 1 Super Incubator and 1 Star Piece
